equation_narrative.headline: Polar representation shifts to positive charge prediction; lysine narrowly defeats threonine
equation_narrative.story: Through layers 1-23, the model assembles a representation of position 55 that is consistently polar-leaning, with the logit lens projecting toward small polar residues (S, T) and hydrophobic residues (L, V) as it reads 8 structural contacts and minimal co-evolutionary signal. The representation character shifts between hydrophobic and polar interpretations through mid-layers, reflecting ambiguity in the local context. At layer 27, the decision phase begins: threonine surges to 58% as T-specific MLP neurons activate, but a catastrophic reversal occurs at layer 33 when attention heads erase 23 logits of threonine support, allowing lysine to claim victory at 27.5% despite threonine being the correct answer at 22%.

perception_phase.summary: Layers 1-23 gather structural and sequence context through 8 structural contacts and 2 co-evolving positions. Early layers (L1-9) show high-projection attention features (F1:5480, F9:5728 with 45-51 proj) encoding local sequence identity and position-specific context. The logit lens fluctuates between hydrophobic residues (L peaks at 33.8% at L19, V at 13.1% at L6-7) and polar residues (S, N, T), reflecting the model's assembly of a mixed chemical environment. By L10-23, MLP neurons begin writing toward threonine (N10:809, N11:1426, N12:3128 with 0.17-0.41 proj each), accumulating +2.5 to +2.7 logits per layer. The representation stabilizes toward small polar/hydrophobic character by L23, with L leading at 26% and T at 10.1%.
perception_phase.context_character: The assembled context by L23 is a mixed polar-hydrophobic environment with moderate burial. The logit lens projects toward small residues (L, T, S) suggesting a compact local structure, with 8 structural contacts providing predominantly hydrophobic signal but insufficient co-evolutionary constraint (only 2 coupled positions) to strongly specify the residue identity.
key_information_sources: Structural contacts: 8 residues within contact distance, read primarily through attention heads at L8-12 (head L8:6 writes +3.9 proj without clear structural focus)
Co-evolutionary signal: minimal (2 positions), insufficient to override local structural interpretation
Early SAE features (L1-9): F1:5480, F1:9146 (45+ proj) encode position-specific context; F9:5728 (50.7 proj) captures mid-layer representation character
MLP accumulation (L10-23): steady threonine support from neurons N10:809 (+0.17), N11:1426 (+0.17), N12:3128 (+0.41), N14:3166 (+0.28) builds +8-10 total logits toward T

decision_phase.summary: The decision crystallizes at L27 when threonine surges from 22.7% to 58% as T-specific MLP neurons fire strongly (N27:4446 writes +1.06, N28:68 writes +0.78, N29:4973 writes +1.31). Threonine peaks at 71.7% at L30, supported by high-projection MLP features (F30:5040, F30:7792 with 41+ proj). However, layer 33 delivers a catastrophic reversal: attention head L29:18 erases -5.2 logits (0.897 structural attention), and L32 heads erase an additional -9.9 logits, collapsing threonine from 50.1% to 22% while lysine and arginine rise to claim 27.5% and 21.5% respectively.
decision_phase.transition: The perception-to-decision boundary occurs at L24-27. At L24, the representation remains ambiguous (L at 26%, S at 23%, T at 10.1%), but by L27, T-specific prediction channels activate: N27:4446 (1.06 proj for T) and SAE features shift from context-encoding to amino-acid-specific voting. The logit lens transitions from reflecting representation character to reflecting actual prediction probabilities as MLP neurons cast explicit votes for threonine.

candidates.narrative: Lysine emerges only in the final layer through a dramatic late-stage surge. It maintains low probability (2-10%) through L29, then explodes to 27.5% at L33 as threonine collapses. The mechanism is primarily subtractive: massive attention-driven erasure of threonine support (L33 attention removes -23.1 logits) creates space for lysine, while MLP neurons at L31-32 provide modest positive support (N31:3170 writes toward charged residues, N32:2672 supports Q/K). Lysine wins by default as the leading positive charge candidate after threonine's collapse.
candidates.key_layers: Dormant through L29 (1.96%), surges at L33 (27.51%)
key_evidence: L33 attention erasure: -23.1 logits removed from T, creating competitive space
N24:129 (MLP eraser, -0.55 proj) votes against T in favor of K (+0.53 proj)
Late positive charge preference emerges as structural erasers remove polar support

candidates.narrative: Threonine is the correct answer and nearly wins. It receives strong MLP support through L25-30, with dedicated T-specific neurons firing at L27-29 (N27:4446 +1.06, N28:68 +0.78, N29:4973 +1.31). Threonine peaks at 71.7% at L30, supported by high-projection SAE features (F30:5040, F30:7792 with 41+ proj). However, catastrophic attention-driven erasure at L29-33 removes the support: L29:18 erases -5.2 logits (0.897 structural attention), L32:16 erases -4.2 logits, and L33 attention removes -23.1 logits total. Threonine collapses from 50.1% to 22% in the final layer.
key_evidence: N27:4446 (MLP, +1.06 proj) — T-specific neuron with strong S/R cross-support
N29:4973 (MLP, +1.31 proj) — strongest T writer, also supports Y/N
F30:5040, F30:7792 (MLP features, 41+ proj) — high-confidence T representation
L29:18 attention head (structural eraser, -5.2 proj, 0.897 structural attn) — catastrophic erasure
L33 attention (total -23.1 logits) — final collapse mechanism

candidates.narrative: Arginine remains a low-probability contender through L29 (3.21%), then rises alongside lysine in the final layers to claim 21.5% at L33. Like lysine, arginine benefits from threonine's collapse rather than strong positive evidence. It receives modest MLP support from neurons that favor positive charges (N31:3170 writes +1.15 toward S/R/H, indirectly supporting R). Arginine's late emergence reflects the model's shift toward positive charge preference as structural erasers remove polar support.
key_evidence: N31:3170 (MLP, +1.15 proj toward S/R/H) — indirect R support through charged residue preference
Benefits from same L33 attention erasure that elevates K
Positive charge preference emerges as polar representation is dismantled

candidates.narrative: Leucine dominates the logit lens through the perception phase, peaking at 33.8% at L19 and leading until L24. This reflects the representation's hydrophobic character as the model reads structural contacts, NOT a model prediction. The logit lens projects toward L because the accumulated features through L1-23 correlate with hydrophobic residues. However, L receives strong negative MLP votes in the decision phase (N12:2104 erases -0.35, N14:1657 erases -0.25) and collapses to 6.67% by L33 as the model commits to polar/charged candidates.
candidates.key_layers: Leads L2-24 (peaks 33.8% at L19), collapses L24-33 (6.67%)
key_evidence: Logit lens artifact: L prominence reflects hydrophobic representation character, not prediction
N12:2104 (MLP eraser, -0.35 proj) — strong anti-L vote favoring N/W
Decision phase: model rejects hydrophobic interpretation in favor of polar/charged

candidates.narrative: Glutamine shows modest presence in mid-layers (peaks 12.4% at L18) as the representation explores polar character, then fades in the decision phase. It receives some MLP support from polar-favoring neurons (N12:2133 erases T in favor of Q with +0.27 proj) but lacks dedicated prediction channels. By L29, Q drops to 0.32% as the model commits to T, K, and R.
key_evidence: N12:2133 (MLP eraser, -0.27 proj from T) — votes for Q (+0.27) over T
Lacks strong decision-phase support; eliminated as model narrows to T/K/R

turning_points.description: The representation shifts from hydrophobic-leaning (L dominant) to polar-leaning as MLP neurons accumulate threonine support. Neurons N10:809, N11:1426, N12:3128, N14:3166 write +0.17 to +0.41 each toward T, building +8-10 total logits. The logit lens shows L peaking at 33.8% at L19, but this reflects the hydrophobic character of structural contacts being read, not a model belief. By L23, the representation has incorporated polar context, with L at 26% and T rising to 10.1%.

Threonine surges as T-specific MLP neurons fire: N27:4446 writes +1.06, N28:68 writes +0.78, N29:4973 writes +1.31. Total MLP contribution at L29 is +10.9 logits toward T. Threonine rises from 22.7% at L27 to 71.7% at L30, supported by high-projection SAE features F30:5040 and F30:7792 (41+ proj each). This is the model's peak confidence in the correct answer, before the catastrophic reversal.

Catastrophic attention-driven erasure collapses threonine and hands victory to lysine. L29:18 (structural eraser, -5.2 proj, 0.897 structural attention) removes major T support. L32 heads (L32:16 -4.2 proj, L32:10 -3.1 proj, L32:9 -2.8 proj) continue the erasure. L33 attention delivers the final blow with -23.1 total logits removed from T. Threonine collapses from 50.1% to 22%, while lysine and arginine rise to 27.5% and 21.5% respectively. The mechanism is primarily subtractive: removing T support rather than building K/R support.

deep_dives.label: Structural attention L8-12
deep_dives.caption: Early attention heads read structural contacts and write context. L8:6 writes +3.9 proj without clear structural focus (0.001 structural attn), suggesting abstract feature computation. These heads assemble the representation that makes the logit lens project toward hydrophobic residues (L, V) in mid-layers.

deep_dives.label: SAE features L1-18 (perception)
deep_dives.caption: Early SAE features encode position-specific context and representation character. F1:5480, F1:9146 (45+ proj) capture initial context. F9:5728 (50.7 proj) represents mid-layer character. F18:9851 (24.7 proj) shows late perception features. These are NOT prediction channels—they encode what the model has learned about this position's environment.

deep_dives.label: MLP neurons L12-23 (T accumulation)
deep_dives.caption: Mid-layer MLPs steadily accumulate threonine support. N12:3128 (+0.41), N14:3166 (+0.28), N17:846 (+0.68), N18:691 (+0.40), N20:1365 (+0.30), N21:453 (+0.54) each write toward T. Total contribution: +8-10 logits. This is where the model begins to favor T over the hydrophobic interpretation suggested by structural contacts.

deep_dives.label: MLP neurons L27-30 (T surge)
deep_dives.caption: Decision-phase MLPs fire T-specific neurons with high confidence. N27:4446 (+1.06), N28:68 (+0.78), N29:4973 (+1.31), N30:3432 (+0.89) are dedicated T writers. L29 contributes +10.9 total logits. These neurons have high T-specificity and drive threonine to 71.7% at L30. This is the model's correct answer before the reversal.

deep_dives.label: SAE features L30-33 (decision)
deep_dives.caption: Late SAE features show the decision and reversal. F30:5040, F30:7792 (41+ proj) are high-confidence T features at the peak. F33:6423, F33:4166 (105, 99 proj) represent the final state after attention erasure. The dramatic shift in feature character reflects the catastrophic reversal from T to K.

deep_dives.label: Attention erasure L29-33
deep_dives.caption: Structural attention heads erase threonine support in the final layers. L29:18 (-5.2 proj, 0.897 structural attn), L31:18 (-2.6 proj, 0.842 structural attn), L32:16 (-4.2 proj, 0.105 structural attn), L32:9 (-2.8 proj, 0.917 structural attn), L32:10 (-3.1 proj, 0.564 local attn). Total L33 attention: -23.1 logits. This is the mechanism of failure—the model dismantles its correct answer.

equation_narrative.resolution: The model correctly assembles a polar-leaning representation and identifies threonine as the answer, reaching 71.7% confidence at L30 through strong MLP support from T-specific neurons. However, structural attention heads at L29-33 catastrophically erase this support, removing -23.1 logits in the final layer and collapsing threonine to 22%. Lysine wins at 27.5% not through strong positive evidence, but by default as the leading positive charge candidate after threonine's collapse. The failure mechanism is attention-driven erasure reading structural contacts that apparently favor charged residues over the correct polar answer, overriding the MLP neurons' correct inference.
